any tips on writing a book i have a great idea for a book but i need some tips to start writing thnx start with what you know about writing and run with it outlining what you want would be a good start though don't pepper it with details just a rough draft on what you want to work with for your book pace yourself this isn't a race to see whom can get a book done the fastest take breaks often by scheduling yourself a couple of weeks off writing is a lonely profession and a tough one only the seriously dedicated can actually make it through this literary miasma in one piece without falling apart in the process good luck Cleveland Browns Extreme Programming Screenplay 2000 Australian Grand Prix Marathon (sport) Indianapolis 500 Red Hot Chili Peppers Fast bowling Triathlon Knife Tina Turner Bee Gees Hendrick Motorsports National Football League Pittsburgh Steelers Giancarlo Fisichella Fernando Alonso Drill bit Athletics at the 2004 Summer Olympics - Men's 400 metres Endgame Charles Bukowski Japanese poetry Association of Tennis Professionals Compiler optimization New England Patriots 24 Hours of Le Mans Types of bowlers in cricket Lake Speed The History of the Decline and Fall of the Roman Empire The Body (Short Story) Carolina Panthers Black pepper CPU design Individual time trial New York Giants Equine conformation Road bicycle racing Samuel Beckett Theory of conduct Repouss__ and chasing Snooker MTV2 Penske Racing Craps Paul W. S. Anderson New York Knicks 2005 Hungarian Grand Prix Wonderland (McFly album) Sailing Seabiscuit Literary criticism Diamond Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Billiards Money Idli Aesthetic Realism New York Yankees September 11, 2001 attacks Pattern language CPU cache Good Morning, Vietnam Eli and the Thirteenth Confession Canadian literature Paintball Great Teacher Onizuka Quicksort Year of the Spider Bicycling terminology Neopets The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie 2005 Belgian Grand Prix Consensus decision-making Bangladeshi cricket team in